"Capra L.","Abrupt climatic changes as triggering mechanisms of massive volcanic collapses",2006,"Journal of Volcanology and Geothermal Research","155","3-4",,"329","333",,,10.1016/j.jvolgeores.2006.04.009,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-33745877181&partnerID=40&md5=62271d89d09bb8a0ae987e05055e2f0d","Instituto de Geografía, UNAM, CU Coyoacan, 04510 Mexico DF, Mexico","Capra, L., Instituto de Geografía, UNAM, CU Coyoacan, 04510 Mexico DF, Mexico","Abrupt climate change can trigger volcanic collapses, phenomena that cause the destruction of the entire sector of a volcano, including its summit. During the past 30 ka, major volcanic collapses occurred just after main glacial peaks that ended with rapid deglaciation. Glacial debuttressing, load discharge and fluid circulation coupled with the post-glacial increase of humidity and heavy rains can activate the failure of unstable edifices. Furthermore, significant global warming can be responsible for the collapse of ice-capped unstable volcanoes, an unpredictable hazard that in few minutes can bury inhabited areas. © 2006.","global warming; volcanic collapse","Atmospheric humidity; Climate change; Failure (mechanical); Glaciers; Ice; Rain; Structural geology; Ice-capped unstable volcanoes; Rapid deglaciation; Unstable edifices; Volcanic collapses; Volcanoes; climate change; climate effect; global warming; natural hazard; volcanism",,,,,,"Acocella, V., Modes of sector collapse of volcanic cones: insights from analogue experiments (2005) Journal of Geophysical Research, 110 (B02205); Alley, R.B., Mayewski, P.A., Sowers, T., Stuiver, M., Taylor, K.C., Clark, P.U., Holocene climatic instability: a prominent, widespread event 8200 years ago (1997) Geology, 25, pp. 483-486; Alley, R.B., Clark, P.U., The deglaciation of the northern hemisphere: a global perspective (1999) Annual Review of Earth and Planetary Sciences, 27, pp. 149-182; Alloway, B.D., Neall, V.E., Vucetich, C.G., Another prehistoric debris avalanche deposit recognized from ancestral Egmont volcano (1986) International Volcanological Congress, New Zealand, p. 2; Caballero, L., Capra, L., (2004) Textural characteristics of the 28,000 yr. BP debris avalanche deposit of Nevado de Toluca volcano, , IAVCEI-General Assembly 2004 ""Volcanism and its Impact on Society"", Pucon, Chile, November 15th-19th; Capra, L., Macias, J.L., Scott, K.M., Abrams, M., Garduño-Monroy, V.H., Debris avalanche and debris flow transformed from collapses in the Trans-Mexican Volcanic Belt, Mexico-behavior, and implication for hazard assessment (2002) Journal of Volcanology and Geothermal Research, 113, pp. 81-110; Carrasco-Nuñez, G., Vallance, J.W., Rose, W.I., A voluminous avalancheinduced lahar from Citlaltepetl volcano, Mexico: implications for hazard assessment (1993) Journal of Volcanology and Geothermal Research, 59, pp. 35-46; Clapperton, C.M., Late Quaternary glacier fluctuations in the Andes: testing the synchrony of global change (1998) Mountain Glaciation. Quaternary Proceedings, 6, pp. 65-73. , Owen L.A. (Ed), John Wiley & Sons, Chichester; Clavero, J.E., Sparks, R.S.J., Huppert, H.E., Geological constraints on the emplacement mechanism of the Parinacota debris avalanche, northern Chile (2002) Bulletin of Volcanology, 64 (1), pp. 40-54; Clavero, J.E., Sparks, R.S.J., Evolution and volcanic hazards of Taapaca volcanic complex, central Andes of northern Chile (2004) Journal of the Geological Society (London), 161, pp. 603-618; Denton, G.H., Hendy, C., Younger Dryas ag advance of Franz Josef glacier in the Southern Alps of New Zealand (1994) Science, 264, pp. 1434-1437; Feeley, T.C., Davidson, J.P., Armendia, A., The volcanic and magmatic evolution of volcan Ollaue, a high-K, late Quaternary stratovolcano in the Andean Central Volcanic Zone (1993) Journal of Volcanology and Geothermal Research, 54, pp. 221-245; Francis, P.W., Wells, G.L., Landsat thematic mapper observation of debris avalanche deposits in central Andes (1988)